<dl id="n36107f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36107f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36107f"> 107(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Place du Temple</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It was Louis VII. also who granted to the Templars the piece of marshland on the left bank of the Seine on which the Paris Temple, the headquarters of the order in Europe, was built &hellip; <font color="green">[n1]</font> It &hellip; was &hellip; pulled down under the Empire in 1811. Its site is occupied by <mark>the Place du Temple</mark>. <small> &ldquo;PARIS&rdquo; <a name="EBPS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBPS"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 815b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
